{You know you may be in slam territory, but first you need to establish trumps. So you bid 3\D as a transfer and almost faint when partner jumps to 4\H, showing a super-accept. Now  

You know you may be in slam territory, but first you need to establish trumps. So you bid 3\D as a transfer and almost faint when partner jumps to 4\H, showing a super-accept. Now 

Check for Aces with Blackwood, partner replies 5\S. What next? 

You know you may be in slam territory, but first you need to establish trumps. So you bid 3\D as a transfer and almost faint when partner jumps to 4\H, showing a super-accept. Now 

Check for Aces with Blackwood, partner replies 5\S. What next?

Partner shows three Aces. You can't consider a Grand Slam, so bid 6\H.

The contract would be 6\H played by South.

North plays 6\H. East leads the \D8, on which West plays the \D9. You win the \DK.

Loser List: \S = 0 : \H = 0 : \D = 2 : \C = 0 :: Total = 2

If you look just at the South and North hands you would think this was a pretty easy slam to make. Pull trumps and play three rounds of \Ds, and as long as the \Ds split 3-2 you make twelve tricks. But when you consider the \D8 opening lead you realize that it won't happen. The missing \Ds are Q J 10 9 and 8. The ONLY combination from which East would lead the \D8 is when he has a singleton. So the \Ds won't be splitting and you need a different plan. 

You need to get a \D discard somewhere, and dummy's third \S will take care of one of <b>YOUR</b> \D losers. But then to establish <b>YOUR</b> hand you are going to have to ruff all 3 \C losers. 

Play the \CA and ruff a \C. Enter your hand with the \H10 and ruff another \C high. Back to your hand with the \HJ and ruff another \C high. Dummy is out of trumps but there is still one more in a defender's hand. So come to your hand with the \SQ and pull the last trump, discarding a \D from dummy.

With all the trumps pulled cash dummy's 2 \Ss and your \DA, then give up a \D at the last trick.

This isn't strictly a dummy-reversal since you actually used your own hand to pull trumps and dummy's trumps for ruffing.

However it's a "role reversal", you pulled trumps with the short-trump hand and took three ruffs in the long-trump hand.

But call it whatever you like, that's the way to make this Deal.}
[Play "W"]D8

